   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1660_brd_ac_22_r.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>الله اکبر</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div1" corresp="#orig_div1">
            <p>God is great</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="right margin">
            <p>
               <stamp type="seal">
                  <mentioned>
                     <persName ref="#nawazishKhan">
                        <unclear>نوازش</unclear>
                         خان</persName>
                     <unclear>مرید</unclear>
                      حضرت محمد
                     <persName ref="#aurangzebAlamgir">اورنگ
                        <unclear>زیب</unclear>
                         عالمگیر </persName>
                      بادشاه غازی
                     <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                        <num>۱۰۷۰</num>
                     </date>
                  </mentioned>
               </stamp>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><persName ref="#nawazishKhan"><unclear>Nawazish</unclear> Khan</persName> <unclear>disciple</unclear> of Lord Muhammad <persName ref="#aurangzebAlamgir">Aurang<unclear>zeb</unclear> Alamgir</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_badshah">Badshah</ref> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_ghazi">Ghazi</ref> <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">1070</date><note>A very clear impression of the same seal is found on <ref type="document" target="#lf_pDas_1660_brd_ac_ii">1660 Order of Nawazish Khan to Purshottam Das granting a house</ref>. Gaps in the reading of the seal impression are supplied through comparison.</note></mentioned></stamp></p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>زبدة الاقران
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">پرسوتم</persName>
                چودری و
               <persName ref="#parasRam">پرسرام</persName>
                قانونگوی پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دهار</placeName>
                بعنایت و
               <lb/>مهربانی امیدوار بوده بدانند عرضه داشتی که درینولا ارسالداشته بودند
               <lb/>رسید حقیقت مشروحاً مفهوم گردید انچه در باب معمار بجهته سنگ موضع
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="#nawasa">نواسه</placeName>
                نوشته بودند معمار فرستاده شد انچه در باب چونه پزان و بیلداران
               <lb/>برای بند تالاب
               <placeName ref="#ratnagra">رتناگره</placeName>
                نوشته بودند پار سال بجهة کندن تالاب 
               <del>انها</del>
               <add>
                  <unclear>او</unclear>
               </add>
               <lb/>دو صد بیلدار جمع شده بودند باید که الحال هم هر قدر بیلدار در کار باشند
               <lb/>سر براه نمایند و چونه پزان انجا در انجا آید چونه سر براه خواهند کرد انچه در باب
               <lb/>داروغه و مشرف
               <add>بند مذکور</add>
               <note>This phrase is added above the line.</note>
                نوشته بودند دازوغگی
               <note>This appears to be a misspelling for دروغگی, i.e. 'daroghagi', meaning superintendency.</note>
                بعهده
               <persName ref="#muhammadHashim">محمد هاشم</persName>
                شقدار انجا است
               <lb/>و مشرف هم از 
               <app>
                  <rdg cert="high">سه</rdg>
                  <rdg cert="low">سنه</rdg>
               </app>
               <num>۳</num>
                بندی خود مقرر خواهد نمود درین باب تاکید دانند
               <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                  <num>۳۰</num>
                   رمضان سنه
                  <num>۱۰۷۰</num>
               </date>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p>
               <lb/>Eminent among Contemporaries
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam [Das]</persName>
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_chaudhri">chaudhri</ref> and
               <persName ref="#parasRam">Paras Ram</persName>
               <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qanungo">qanungo</ref> of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref>
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>
               ,
               <lb/>being hopeful of favour and kindness, know that the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_arzdasht">ʿarzdasht</ref>, which they had sent recently,
               <lb/>has arrived. The situation explained was understood. Regarding what they had
               written in the matter of the mason on account of the stone of village
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="#nawasa">Nawasa</placeName>
               , the mason was sent. In the matter of the lime burners<note>Known as chuna-paz in
                  Persian, these workers burnt limestone to produce quicklime, a key ingredient of
                  mortar.</note> and the diggers
               <lb/>for the dam of
               <placeName ref="#ratnagra">Ratnagarh's [Ratnagra's]</placeName>
                water tank, which they had written about,
               <lb/>two hundred diggers had been gathered last year for the digging of their [his]
               water tank. Now, too, it is necessary that [they] supply all diggers who [are able
               to] work
               <lb/>and the lime burners of that place will supply quick lime. [Regarding] that
               which they had written
               <lb/>in the matter of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_darogha">darogha</ref> and
                  <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mushrif">mushrif</ref> of the aforesaid dam, the
               superintendency is the obligation of
               <persName ref="#muhammadHashim">Muhammad Hashim</persName>
               , the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_shiqdar">shiqdar</ref> of that place,
               <lb/>and the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mushrif">mushrif</ref> too will be
               appointed out of his own <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sihbandi">sih-bandi</ref>.
               In this matter they shall know it settled.
               <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">30 Ramzan year 1070</date>
               . </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="bottom right margin">
            <p>هو</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div4" corresp="#orig_div4">
            <p>He [God] is</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div5" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="right margin">
            <p>
               <lb/>حسب المسطور مقرر شناسند بیلدار
               <gap/>
                باشد
               <lb/>معمور از حضور فرستاده شده چونه
               <unclear>پز</unclear>
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دهار</placeName>
                چه شده
               <lb/>باو مقرر نماید که مصالح طیار نماید و اگر در
               <placeName ref="#nalcha">نعلچه</placeName>
                امده است
               <lb/>بمتصدی
               <placeName ref="#nalcha">نعلچه</placeName>
                نوشته شده که او را بفرستاد خواهد فرستاد </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div5" corresp="#orig_div5">
            <p>
               <lb/>Know it settled as written. The digger
               <gap/>
                shall be.
               <lb/>The mason having been sent from the Lord, whatever lime burners there are [in]
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>
               <lb/>appoint [them] to [work under] him so that the public conveniences are prepared.
               And if he has come to
               <placeName ref="#nalcha">Nalcha</placeName>
               ,
               <lb/>the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mutasaddi">mutasaddi</ref> of
               <placeName ref="#nalcha">Nalcha</placeName>
                has been written to that he should be sent, [and] he will be sent. </p>
         </div>
         <pb n="1v" facs="lf_pDas_1660_brd_ac_22_v.jpg"/>
         <div xml:id="orig_div6" xml:lang="per" type="clericalNotes" rend="right margin">
            <p>
               <lb/>نقل
               <unclear>سیاهه</unclear>
               <lb/>بتاریخ
               <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">
                  <num>۳۰</num>
                   رمضان سنه
                  <num>۱۰۷۰</num>
               </date>
               <lb/>نقلدفتر دیوان رسید
               <g ref="#faqt">فقط</g>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div6" corresp="#orig_div6">
            <p>
               <lb/><unclear>Register</unclear> copy
               <lb/>On the date <date calendar="#hijri-qamri">30 Ramzan year 1070</date>
               <lb/>the copy of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_daftar">daftar</ref> of the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_diwan">diwan</ref> arrived.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div7" xml:lang="hin" type="laterAddition" rend="top left">
            <p>
               <lb rend="empty"/>
               <placeName ref="#ratnagra">रतनागर</placeName>
                तलाब का
               <lb rend="empty"/>
               <unclear>छ</unclear>
               ह तमाम
               <unclear>कीए</unclear>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div7" corresp="#orig_div7">
            <p>
               <lb rend="empty"/><placeName ref="#ratnagra">Ratnagra</placeName> water tank's
               <lb rend="empty"/><gap/> <unclear>made</unclear> complete
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
